Analyze AO Stage Micrometer from BX61

J. R. Minter

Started: 2013-07-16, Last modified: 2019-05-30

Back to ImageJ

I had recorded an image on the Olympus BX-16 microscope at 10X. The metadata from the original image is shown below.

Metadata from SIS Viewer

The image (reduced to 8 bits/pix) is shown below.

The image reduced to 8 bits per pixel. One large divison is \(100\ \mu m\).

After cropping the image to measure just the large divisons and applying an automatic threshold to segment the lines I obtained the image below.

The thresholded image with segments detected.

An enlarged view of the first two lines is shown below.

The first two lines detected.

The measurement data was stored to a .csv file for analysis.

Let’s read in the data

df <-read.csv2("tif/stage-micrometer/BX61-10X-1-AO-micro.csv", sep=',')
library(knitr)
kable(df)

Note that the area of the last measurement is 1 pixel. This is spurious. We need to filter out the last row.

We can do this using base R as shown below

df_good <- df[df$Area>1,]
kable(df_good)
